@anthr76 did you install the qemu binaries ?

`docker run --rm --privileged multiarch/qemu-user-static --reset -p yes`

Try this once

@kaovilai Thank you for at least disclosing that this was written by LLM but please don't post slop in a technical discussion forum. 

More evidence and details are required to believe the root cause analysis here. *Which* xattrs are not supported—`security.selinux`? Why is this not supported on a filesystem-level? What is the supported documentation for that? Is there a bug in virtiofs tracking this? Why does BuildKit "need" this xattr, and if that's the case, how does Podman-on-macOS work *at all*? 

Otherwise, it's a weak claim followed by an ad, aka spam. The solution to this minor issue is probably not to throw out *the entirety of Podman* in favor of a brand new vibecoded solution.
